name: Crab Rangoon Pizza
author: AR Community Support
summary: True crab rangoon flavor on a pizza. Easily made to be gluten-free.
ingredients: 1 cup vegetable oil for frying, or as needed
4  (3.5 inch square) wonton wrappers, cut into strips
¼ cup shredded Parmesan cheese, divided
directions: Heat vegetable oil in a deep skillet over medium-high heat; fry wonton strips until crisp, 2 to 4 minutes
Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to drain
Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C)
Spread pizza dough onto a baking sheet
Bake in the preheated oven until slightly brown, about 7 minutes
Mix cream cheese, 1/4 cup green onions, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, and crab together in a bowl; spread onto the pizza crust
Top with mozzarella cheese, remaining Parmesan cheese, fried wonton strips, and remaining green onions
Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is browned and melted, about 8 minutes
Drizzle sweet chile sauce over top
